# 4. 友達想い

Airi: Alright... So we have to find the first panel and guess the name of a tree that looks like...
Airi: The map says that it should be around here somewhere too...
Mizuki: Wait, isn't that it by the base of that tree?
Airi: You're right. It even includes two hints.
Airi: “Hint 1: They are often planted near shrines... Hint 2: Bluebottle butterfly larvae like to eat their leaves...”
Mizuki: It's talking about camphor trees, right?
Airi: Wait, you know the answer?
Mizuki: I remember seeing this in a book and on a quiz show. The answers are supposed to be written on the back, so let's take a look...
Airi: Yup! The answer is, "Camphor trees."
Airi: That's so cool! Do you know a lot about plants, Mizuki?
Mizuki: Not really. I just happened to know this one.
Mizuki: But are Ena and Shizuku gonna be okay? It looked like there were a bunch of bugs over where they were. I hope they don't get into trouble or anything...
Airi: Nah, they should be fine. Ena's tougher than she looks.
Mizuki: Yeah, that's true. Ena is pretty good at looking after people, me included...
Airi: (Wait, this is getting more personal...)
Airi: (This could be a chance to learn more about what's bothering Mizuki... Just gotta find the most opportune moment and ask...!)
Airi: So you all meet up online to make songs as a group? That's gotta be pretty hard sometimes.
Mizuki: It actually isn't. We're all a little weird, but everyone's really nice too so it's pretty fun!
Airi: I see... That's good to hear!
Airi: (Hmm... I guess I won't get any real answers that easily, huh?)
Airi: I'm also pretty glad that you became friends with Ena...
Mizuki: Huh? Why?
Airi: You know how Ena is... She says what's on her mind and can rub people the wrong way, you know...?
Mizuki: Haha. Yeah, totally. Ena can be pretty ruthless sometimes.
Mizuki: We went to this cafe where you can make handicrafts called the sewing lounge the other day...
Mizuki: After I finished drawing a sketch for something I was about to make, she was like, "There's no way this'll turn out cute!"
Airi: Hehe. That's Ena for you.
Mizuki: Yeah, she can be so mean sometimes!
Mizuki: But after that, she sat down with me to think about how to make it better. That's kind of what I really like about her.
Airi: Hehe. I know exactly what you mean. She's done that a few times for me too.
Mizuki: Really? She's helped you before too, Airi?
Airi: Yeah, she has.
Airi: Before I really started getting work as an idol, I was a regular junior high school student and Ena was in the same class as me.
Airi: We didn't really talk much at first, but one day, some of my classmates started making fun of this variety show I appeared in...
Airi: It's not like I was being bullied or anything, but I knew that people were talking about me behind my back. That was when Ena got mad...
Airi: She yelled, "You really think that's funny?!"
Mizuki: Seriously? Man, she really has always been like that then...!
Airi: I know, right? I thanked her for what she did later, but she just replied, "I said that because I didn't like what was going on. That's all..."
Airi: But what she did made me really happy. I'd never seen someone stand up for a stranger like that before...
Airi: Everyone stopped talking about me and I became friends with Ena after that.
Mizuki: That's nice... Actually, that reminds me of something...
Mizuki: E-Enanan?! What are you doing here?!
Ena: I came to give Yuki a piece of my mind!
Mizuki: Whenever she sees that someone's going through something, she just comes right out with it, you know?
Airi: Yeah, exactly! It's like she knows what to do when it really matters, which is why...
Airi: If there's something bothering you, Mizuki, I think you should talk to Ena about it. I'm sure she can help you.
Mizuki: Wait, hold on...
Ena: <And you're the one that's always talking about getting different perspectives on things. Seeing a pretty landscape might even give you some ideas for the video, you know?>
Ena: <Hey, stay on topic. I'm the one that's asking you if you want to come on this picnic.>
Mizuki: (So that's why she tried so hard to get me to go on this picnic...)
Mizuki: (Ena, you little fox...)
Mizuki: (But I get it now... She's genuinely worried about me.)
Nene: *Huff*... *Huff*... *Huff*...
Rui: You're doing great, Nene! I'm getting plenty of good data too!
Nene: No... No more... I'm taking these off... And taking a break...
Rui: Okay, let's take a break.
Rui: While you do that, I'll be trying out some of the other new props I brought.
Rui: Hehehe... Now, which do I start with first...
Nene: (How's Rui not tired? He's been lugging all that stuff the entire day...?)
Rui: Oh no!
Nene: Huh? What is it?
Rui: I forgot to bring the "Star Training Suit"...! I even brought the rope for it too...
Nene: Star Training Suit? What's that...?
Rui: It's a sort of powered exoskeleton. It helps the user run, carry things and move around more easily.
Rui: In other words! Whoever wears this will be able to run, jump, move around and even carry massive objects while performing with little to no effort!
Rui: It still needs a few adjustments, but by tying this rope to Tsukasa, he could fly from one side of the stage to the other in one leap... Such a shame...
Nene: Rui, please try to remember that we're a theatre troupe, not a circus, okay...?
